.TH "libnvme_ctrl_owner" 9 "libnvme_ctrl_owner" "June 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvme_ctrl_owner \- Registered orchestrator owner of a controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" libnvme_ctrl_owner
.BI "(libnvme_ctrl_t c "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
Controller instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Looks up the controller's "owner" entry in the ownership registry.  In a
build without fabrics support this always returns NULL.
.SH "RETURN"
a newly allocated owner string (the caller frees), or NULL if the
controller is unowned, local (non-fabrics), or the registry is unreadable.
